    "note": "No one-photon excitation/emission spectrum is published for ASAP1/ASAP2s: the eLife 2017 paper reports only two-photon excitation spectra (Fig. 1E) and the St-Pierre 2014 ASAP1 paper reports none. ASAP1's fluorophore is cpsfGFP-OPT, a circularly permuted superfolder GFP, so the FPbase Superfolder GFP excitation/emission curve is used as a fluorophore proxy. ASAP2s (ASAP1 + R415Q) shares this fluorophore. Replaces a curve that was a verbatim copy of the FPbase EGFP spectrum."
